Short Description:
The American Association on Intellectual and Developmental Disabilities (AAIDD) is a non-profit professional organization established in 1876. It is dedicated to advancing the field of intellectual and developmental disabilities through research, effective practices, and the promotion of universal human rights. Headquartered in Silver Spring, Maryland, AAIDD is the oldest and largest interdisciplinary organization in this field, with members across the United States and over 50 other countries.

AAIDD's mission focuses on enhancing the capacity of professionals, promoting inclusivity, and ensuring effective governance. The organization provides professional development through an Online Learning platform with over 300 accredited courses. It also publishes the *American Journal on Intellectual and Developmental Disabilities*, along with various journals, books, and webinars that contribute to the advancement of knowledge and practices in the field. AAIDD plays a vital role in shaping policies and standards, including contributions to global health guidelines.

Parse Biosciences is a Seattle-based biotechnology company founded in 2018, specializing in scalable, instrument-free single-cell sequencing solutions. The company is known for its proprietary Evercode™ platform, which enhances high-throughput RNA workflows. With around 110 employees, Parse serves over 3,000 customers in more than 40 countries, focusing on advancing single-cell science through innovative combinatorial barcoding technology.

The company provides a range of end-to-end solutions, including Evercode™ Whole Transcriptome Kits for scalable single-cell RNA sequencing, Evercode™ Immune Profiling assays for immunological applications, and the Trailmaker™ Software Suite for cloud-based data analysis. Additionally, the GigaLab service platform supports large-scale project processing. Parse's tools are designed to be flexible and accessible, enabling researchers to explore complex biological systems across various fields, including developmental biology, cancer research, and immunotherapy.

The company specializes in developing advanced swarming unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) and autonomous swarm control systems. Its mission is to enable small teams to mobilize thousands of uncrewed assets in challenging environments, focusing on applications in defense, logistics, communications, sensing, disaster response, and industrial inspections.

Loudoun United FC offers season memberships, single-game tickets, and merchandise, along with community engagement initiatives and player development programs. Escape is a French cybersecurity startup that focuses on API security through AI-powered Dynamic Application Security Testing (DAST). Founded by Tristan Kalos and Antoine Carossio in 2018, the company emerged from Y Combinator's winter 2023 cohort and has raised $3.9 million in seed funding. Its team includes experts with backgrounds in AI research and security engineering.

Escape develops agentless DAST tools that integrate into modern development pipelines to dynamically scan APIs during runtime. The company specializes in identifying business logic vulnerabilities, such as Broken Object Level Authorization and access control issues. Its proprietary AI technology enhances coverage by simulating cyberattacks and analyzing application execution context. Escape supports both GraphQL and REST APIs and offers seamless integration with developer workflows, including tools like Snyk. The company aims to provide quick setup for secure API development, targeting developers and Fortune 1000 companies.
